article.description: — Max Shulga scored 17 points as VCU beat Samford 75-65 on Friday night.
article.headline: Shulga's 17 lead VCU past Samford 75-65
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- — Max Shulga scored 17 points as VCU beat Samford 75-65 on Friday night. Shulga shot 5 for 9 (4 for 7 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line for the Rams (1-1). Zeb Jackson added 13 points while shooting 5 for 9, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc, and he also had seven assists and four steals. Jason Nelson shot 4 for 10 (0 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with 11 points, while adding six steals. The Bulldogs (0-2) were led by Jermaine Marshall, who posted 20 points, 10 rebounds and four steals. A.J. Staton-McCray added 16 points and three steals for Samford. Achor Achor also had six points. NEXT UP VCU's next game is Wednesday against Radford at home. Samford hosts Mississippi College on Tuesday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
